author: stsp
msg: Fix issue #3486, "attempt to add tree conflict that already exists", again.
Hopefully this is the last time we'll need to deal with this.
* subversion/libsvn_client/merge.c
(tree_conflict): Always check for an existing tree conflict before
attempting to record a new one. If one already exists, do nothing.
Multiple attempts to flag a conflict can happen when a merge performs
multiple editor drives, because of a gap in the range of eligible
revisions. There is no point in aborting the entire merge because of this.
The user will have to sort out the conflict anyway.

author: hwright
msg: Introduce a scratch_pool into organize_lock_targets().  This is a followup to
r1058237.  This does *not* decrease the memory footprint, since the same
pool is being used for scratch and result by the callers, but it does better
follow our recent patterns.
* subversion/libsvn_client/locking_commands.c
(organize_lock_targets): Add a scratch pool, and use it.
(svn_client_lock, svn_client_unlock): Update callers.
